  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 666 (st3286): __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ dict-presence (in-place augmented assignment)."
    - "All values False — hash objects, UUID, Struct, and socket types have no in-place arithmetic protocol."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __iadd__, __isub__, or __imul__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not support in-place augmented assignment operations."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no in-place arithmetic protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

